text: they look so lush and indulgent 😍 when I bake softer, cakey cookies I often find that within a few hours post-baking, they get too soft and crumbly. Would you have any advice for this?

answers.text: @culinary.conundrum hmm usually that’s because they absorb the air around them! Usually the best way is to either re bake them or to keep them in as airtight containers as possible, such as mason jars or ziplock bags 😋
